ng in crypt in OS or in HS for example.  Pets for clerics are a joke, but clerics are not meant to be damage dealers.<br><br>4) This was obviously written before Blessing of Aego came into the game, a good change which moved clerics away from the tedium of buffing that shamans still suffer.<br><br>5) We have numerous items that we can use to invis- larrikan's mask, potions, gnomish invis devices.  And if invis breaks, just DB /ooc the train and run it.  Casters get invis because they're more fragile, druids &amp; shamans don't get itu.  With improved itu, a cleric is often a great corpse-dragger in deadside of lguk for example- not to mention that most keyed dungeons are largely full of see-invis mobs.  Also, there is an overwhelming perception by many that clerics are the best healers for every situation, everyone wants one even when we aren't really needed.<br><br>6)  CH is arguably the most powerful spell in game.  It's true that shamans are more valuable in xp areas, because of slow, canni, torpor, debuffs etc.  But in challenging areas where mobs cannot be slowed, harmtouch etc, a cleric is almost essential.  Not to mention that in terms of raids, clerics often make or break a raid's success.<br><br>7)  We have an amazing undead-only dot, and judgement, and can actually solo half-decently in the right areas.  <br><br>8 ) Druids have seasons, shamans have shadoo, and we get individual buffs for all resists- mages have elemental blankets they can summon, chanters have GMR.  Every spell-class has some form of resist buff, that seems fine.<br><br>9) Heh, any idea how unbalanced this would be in pvp?  Versus anything but manaburn it makes it impossible to kill a cleric, it's hard enough as it is.  <br><br>Other classes being able to heal/rez is intentional- VI want to encourage grouping, but don't want to give one class a set of abilities that makes them indispensable.  If you only gave clerics rezzes, if you gave only them the best small heals, that would make them indispensable in certain areas, just as if you only gave slow to shamans.  As it is, clerics are the only choice for primary healer in an AE group for example, WoV/WoR plus remedy/elixir make having one essential.  <br><br>I'm sure whoever wrote that meant well, but those changes would by in large break the class.  Not to say there aren't things that can be improved (/wave CH bug, /wave crap AA abilities), but overall there isn't a whole lot to gripe about that is class-specific. <p>Taranna Dhossarim60th Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=872.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=872.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=872.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.threadControl?topicID=872.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=872.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=872.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub83.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"